{
  "stem": "15732.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that was so instilled from childhood in me that I always feel that I have to do it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My grandmother died early.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was, I think, five or six when she died.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember her only as a very sick woman, very good, good-hearted, nice, always good to the grandchildren.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All grannies are a dream to the grandchildren, but not much more about it that I can say.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I started my schooling in Chernivitsi in a public school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "School days are not a very pleasant memory for me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because in school, we had to interact with non-Jewish Romanians who basically always showed their disdain and looked down to us because we were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the staff, the teacher staff, was non-Jewish, too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That is primary school and later on in high school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember any particular incidents in primary school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yet I remember quite a bit of my high school years, which were quite unpleasant in that respect, that in subjects that I was really excelled myself and was very good, I never got the, first the best mention or the best mark.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because she couldn't-- the teacher just wouldn't give a Jewish girl the same-- the best mark.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had several [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] happenings with my-- with the headmistress, who was a particular nasty person, who in an assembly once called me out for no reason whatsoever to look if I have-- if my eyebrows are not tinted.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was at that time maybe a girl of 12 or 13 who never would put-- I wore-- it was not-- at that, makeup was not used as here.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it was only part of a constant-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] how would I say-- a constant putting down everyone that was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
